  "suggestion": "[social-cognition+cognitive-consistency-theory+Festinger-1957+self-perception-theory] IMPLEMENT NOW — Cognitive Dissonance Detector (Festinger 1957). When stimulus reveals a belief-behavior gap or belief-belief conflict, compute dissonance = Σ|belief_i × belief_j| × personalRelevance. Three resolution strategies map to attractor basin capture: (1) rationalization (high commitment → justify behavior), (2) trivialization (low importance → downweight), (3) belief-change (low commitment + high PE → update belief). This short-circuits the current free-energy pipeline for consistency-relevant stimuli. Implementation: add computeDissonance(situation) → {score, strategy}; inject before domain template; when strategy=rationalization output behavior='justify-prior-choice'; when strategy=belief-change shift dominant attractor toward 'update-belief'. Covers: cognitive-dissonance, self-perception theory, post-decision regret, identity-protective cognition. — Math: D = Σ_{i≠j} |b_i × b_j| × importance_ij; commitment c = history.length/5; strategy = c>0.6 ? 'rationalize' : importance<0.3 ? 'trivialize' : 'update'; [existential-psychology+evolutionary-psychology+cultural-psychology+Greenberg-Pyszczynski-Solomon] Terror Management Theory (Greenberg 1986) as Mortality Salience Override. When death cues are salient, the existential buffer activates — people defend worldview and pursue self-esteem striving rather than proximal needs. Mathematically: MS_score = death_cue_density(desc) × (1 − attachment_security), where attachment_security = 1 − person.arousal × SHUTDOWN_indicator. When MS_score > 0.5: override need-space entirely, shifting dominant need to 'meaning/worldview-defense', override emotion to 'existential-anxiety', behavior to 'worldview-affirmation' or 'self-esteem-striving'. Death cues = {'death', 'die', 'mortal', 'funeral', 'kill', 'end', 'annihilat', 'terminal', 'legacy', 'afterlife'}. This covers a large unexplained variance in cultural, religious, political, and risk-taking behavior that the current pipeline misses entirely. — Math: MS = cue_count/total_tokens × (1 − attachment_security); if MS > 0.5: response.rootCause = 'TMT: mortality-salience activates existential buffer → worldview-defense'; response.behavior = self_esteem > 0.5 ? 'worldview-affirmation' : 'death-denial'; [self-control+cognitive-resource-theory+Baumeister-1998+dual-process-theory] Self-Regulation Resource Depletion (Baumeister 1998) — Ego Depletion as Capacity Modifier. Self-control draws on a limited resource. Model capacity = 1 − Σ(prior_effort_i × recency_weight_i), where effort is inferred from person.history tasks (effortful = tasks containing 'resist', 'suppress', 'control', 'decide', 'focus', 'concentrate'). When capacity < 0.3: (1) shift all need-priors toward immediate-gratification needs (pleasure, belonging), (2) reduce attractor basin depths for deliberate/planful attractors by 0.5×, (3) amplify impulsive attractor depths by 1.5×. This gives the model temporal context — the same stimulus gets a different response depending on prior resource consumption. Integration point: compute depletion after polyvagal gate, before free energy; multiply scaledPrecision for deliberate needs by capacity. — Math: cap = 1 − min(Σ(effort_flag_i × 0.8^i for i in history), 0.9); if cap < 0.3: pleasure.precision *= 2.0; achievement.precision *= cap; autonomy.precision *= cap; deep_attractor.depth for 'deliberate' *= cap",
